DAY 10 - METHODS USING ATTRIBUTES

A method can use attributes stored in the object.

Example:

class Student:

    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

    def study(self):
        print(self.name, "is studying")

student1 = Student("Ishu")

student1.study()

Output:

Ishu is studying

Important:

Methods can access object data using self.attribute.

Examples:

self.name
self.brand
self.age

